  "summaries": [
    {
      "actionDate": "2026-01-27",
      "actionDesc": "Reported to House",
      "text": "<p><strong>Deporting Fraudsters Act of 2026</strong></p><p>This bill makes certain acts related to public benefits fraud grounds for (1) barring a&nbsp;non-U.S. national (<em>alien</em> under federal law) from admission into the United States, or (2) deporting the individual. The bill also makes such an individual ineligible for immigration enforcement relief, including relief for an individual in danger of subjection to torture.</p><p>Specifically, this bill applies to individuals who have been convicted of, admit to having committed, or admit to acts which constitute certain offenses. Offenses covered by this bill include (1) fraud involving Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits, (2) fraud involving Social Security benefits, (3) fraud involving programs that receive federal funds, and (4) the production of fraudulent identification documents.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-03-02T14:28:48Z",
      "versionCode": "07"
    }
  ]
}